  <Name>k__BackingField: 1 Timothy
  fancyName: 
  nickname: 1ti
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 51ee3e37f5ded7941ab6216610f6fc67, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: Greetings from Paul
      content: '  This letter is from Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus, appointed
        by the command of God our Savior and Christ Jesus, who gives us hope.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Warnings against False Teachings
      content: 'I am writing to Timothy, my true son in the faith.May God the Father
        and Christ Jesus our Lord give you grace, mercy, and peace.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When I left for Macedonia, I urged you to stay there in Ephesus and
        stop those whose teaching is contrary to the truth. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t let them waste their time in endless discussion of myths
        and spiritual pedigrees. These things only lead to meaningless speculations,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        which don\u2019t help people live a life of faith in God.[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:4a '
        content: Greek <b>in myths and endless genealogies, which cause speculation.</b>
      - number: '1:4b '
        content: Greek <b>a stewardship of God in faith.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'The purpose of my instruction is that all believers would be filled
        with love that comes from a pure heart, a clear conscience, and genuine faith. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But some people have missed this whole point. They have turned away
        from these things and spend their time in meaningless discussions. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They want to be known as teachers of the law of Moses, but they don\u2019t
        know what they are talking about, even though they speak so confidently.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We know that the law is good when used correctly. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the law was not intended for people who do what is right. It
        is for people who are lawless and rebellious, who are ungodly and sinful,
        who consider nothing sacred and defile what is holy, who kill their father
        or mother or commit other murders. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The law is for people who are sexually immoral, or who practice homosexuality,
        or are slave traders,[[COMMENT(0)]] liars, promise breakers, or who do anything
        else that contradicts the wholesome teaching '
      comments:
      - number: '1:10 '
        content: Or <b>kidnappers.</b>
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Gratitude for God\u2019s Mercy"
      content: 'that comes from the glorious Good News entrusted to me by our blessed
        God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I thank Christ Jesus our Lord, who has given me strength to do his
        work. He considered me trustworthy and appointed me to serve him, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'even though I used to blaspheme the name of Christ. In my insolence,
        I persecuted his people. But God had mercy on me because I did it in ignorance
        and unbelief. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Oh, how generous and gracious our Lord was! He filled me with the
        faith and love that come from Christ Jesus.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is a trustworthy saying, and everyone should accept it: \u201CChrist
        Jesus came into the world to save sinners\u201D\u2014and I am the worst of
        them all. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But God had mercy on me so that Christ Jesus could use me as a prime
        example of his great patience with even the worst sinners. Then others will
        realize that they, too, can believe in him and receive eternal life. '
      comments: []
    - title: "Timothy\u2019s Responsibility"
      content: 'All honor and glory to God forever and ever! He is the eternal King,
        the unseen one who never dies; he alone is God. Amen.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Timothy, my son, here are my instructions for you, based on the prophetic
        words spoken about you earlier. May they help you fight well in the Lord\u2019s
        battles. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Cling to your faith in Christ, and keep your conscience clear. For
        some people have deliberately violated their consciences; as a result, their
        faith has been shipwrecked. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Instructions about Worship
      content: '  I urge you, first of all, to pray for all people. Ask God to help
        them; intercede on their behalf, and give thanks for them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Pray this way for kings and all who are in authority so that we can
        live peaceful and quiet lives marked by godliness and dignity. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This is good and pleases God our Savior, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'who wants everyone to be saved and to understand the truth. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For,There is one God and one Mediator who can reconcile God and humanity\u2014the
        man Christ Jesus. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He gave his life to purchase freedom for everyone.This is the message
        God gave to the world at just the right time. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I have been chosen as a preacher and apostle to teach the Gentiles
        this message about faith and truth. I\u2019m not exaggerating\u2014just telling
        the truth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In every place of worship, I want men to pray with holy hands lifted
        up to God, free from anger and controversy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And I want women to be modest in their appearance.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        They should wear decent and appropriate clothing and not draw attention to
        themselves by the way they fix their hair or by wearing gold or pearls or
        expensive clothes. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:9 '
        content: Or <b>to pray in modest apparel.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'For women who claim to be devoted to God should make themselves attractive
        by the good things they do.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Women should learn quietly and submissively. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I do not let women teach men or have authority over them.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Let them listen quietly. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:12 '
        content: Or <b>teach men or usurp their authority.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'For God made Adam first, and afterward he made Eve. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And it was not Adam who was deceived by Satan. The woman was deceived,
        and sin was the result. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Leaders in the Church
      content: "  This is a trustworthy saying: \u201CIf someone aspires to be a
        church leader,[[COMMENT(0)]] he desires an honorable position.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '3:1 '
        content: Or <b>an overseer, </b>or <b>a bishop; </b>also in 3:2, 6.
    - title: 
      content: 'So a church leader must be a man whose life is above reproach. He
        must be faithful to his wife.[[COMMENT(0)]] He must exercise self-control,
        live wisely, and have a good reputation. He must enjoy having guests in his
        home, and he must be able to teach. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:2 '
        content: Or <b>must have only one wife, </b>or <b>must be married only once;
          </b>Greek reads <b>must be the husband of one wife; </b>also in 3:12.
    - title: 
      content: 'He must not be a heavy drinker[[COMMENT(0)]] or be violent. He must
        be gentle, not quarrelsome, and not love money. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:3 '
        content: Greek <b>must not drink too much wine; </b>similarly in 3:8.
    - title: 
      content: 'He must manage his own family well, having children who respect and
        obey him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For if a man cannot manage his own household, how can he take care
        of God\u2019s church?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A church leader must not be a new believer, because he might become
        proud, and the devil would cause him to fall.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:6 '
        content: Or <b>he might fall into the same judgment as the devil.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Also, people outside the church must speak well of him so that he
        will not be disgraced and fall into the devil\u2019s trap.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In the same way, deacons must be well respected and have integrity.
        They must not be heavy drinkers or dishonest with money. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They must be committed to the mystery of the faith now revealed and
        must live with a clear conscience. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Before they are appointed as deacons, let them be closely examined.
        If they pass the test, then let them serve as deacons.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In the same way, their wives[[COMMENT(0)]] must be respected and
        must not slander others. They must exercise self-control and be faithful
        in everything they do.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:11 '
        content: Or <b>the women deacons. </b>The Greek word can be translated <b>women
          </b>or <b>wives.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'A deacon must be faithful to his wife, and he must manage his children
        and household well. '
      comments: []
    - title: The Truths of Our Faith
      content: 'Those who do well as deacons will be rewarded with respect from others
        and will have increased confidence in their faith in Christ Jesus.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am writing these things to you now, even though I hope to be with
        you soon, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'so that if I am delayed, you will know how people must conduct themselves
        in the household of God. This is the church of the living God, which is the
        pillar and foundation of the truth.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Warnings against False Teachers
      content: '  Now the Holy Spirit tells us clearly that in the last times some
        will turn away from the true faith; they will follow deceptive spirits and
        teachings that come from demons. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These people are hypocrites and liars, and their consciences are
        dead.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:2 '
        content: Greek <b>are seared.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'They will say it is wrong to be married and wrong to eat certain
        foods. But God created those foods to be eaten with thanks by faithful people
        who know the truth. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Since everything God created is good, we should not reject any of
        it but receive it with thanks. '
      comments: []
    - title: A Good Servant of Christ Jesus
      content: 'For we know it is made acceptable[[COMMENT(0)]] by the word of God
        and prayer.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:5 '
        content: Or <b>made holy.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'If you explain these things to the brothers and sisters,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Timothy, you will be a worthy servant of Christ Jesus, one who is nourished
        by the message of faith and the good teaching you have followed. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:6 '
        content: Greek <b>brothers.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Do not waste time arguing over godless ideas and old wives\u2019
        tales. Instead, train yourself to be godly. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CPhysical training is good, but training for godliness is much
        better, promising benefits in this life and in the life to come.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This is a trustworthy saying, and everyone should accept it. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This is why we work hard and continue to struggle,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        for our hope is in the living God, who is the Savior of all people and particularly
        of all believers.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:10 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>continue to suffer.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Teach these things and insist that everyone learn them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t let anyone think less of you because you are young. Be
        an example to all believers in what you say, in the way you live, in your
        love, your faith, and your purity. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Until I get there, focus on reading the Scriptures to the church,
        encouraging the believers, and teaching them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do not neglect the spiritual gift you received through the prophecy
        spoken over you when the elders of the church laid their hands on you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Give your complete attention to these matters. Throw yourself into
        your tasks so that everyone will see your progress. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Advice about Widows, Elders, and Slaves
      content: '  Never speak harshly to an older man,[[COMMENT(0)]] but appeal to
        him respectfully as you would to your own father. Talk to younger men as
        you would to your own brothers. '
      comments:
      - number: '5:1 '
        content: Or <b>an elder.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Treat older women as you would your mother, and treat younger women
        with all purity as you would your own sisters.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Take care of[[COMMENT(0)]] any widow who has no one else to care
        for her. '
      comments:
      - number: '5:3 '
        content: Or <b>Honor.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'But if she has children or grandchildren, their first responsibility
        is to show godliness at home and repay their parents by taking care of them.
        This is something that pleases God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now a true widow, a woman who is truly alone in this world, has placed
        her hope in God. She prays night and day, asking God for his help. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the widow who lives only for pleasure is spiritually dead even
        while she lives. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Give these instructions to the church so that no one will be open
        to criticism.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But those who won\u2019t care for their relatives, especially those
        in their own household, have denied the true faith. Such people are worse
        than unbelievers.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A widow who is put on the list for support must be a woman who is
        at least sixty years old and was faithful to her husband.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:9 '
        content: Greek <b>was the wife of one husband.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'She must be well respected by everyone because of the good she has
        done. Has she brought up her children well? Has she been kind to strangers
        and served other believers humbly?[[COMMENT(0)]] Has she helped those who
        are in trouble? Has she always been ready to do good?  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:10 '
        content: "Greek <b>and washed the feet of God\u2019s holy people?</b>"
    - title: 
      content: 'The younger widows should not be on the list, because their physical
        desires will overpower their devotion to Christ and they will want to remarry. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then they would be guilty of breaking their previous pledge. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And if they are on the list, they will learn to be lazy and will
        spend their time gossiping from house to house, meddling in other people\u2019s
        business and talking about things they shouldn\u2019t. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So I advise these younger widows to marry again, have children, and
        take care of their own homes. Then the enemy will not be able to say anything
        against them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For I am afraid that some of them have already gone astray and now
        follow Satan.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If a woman who is a believer has relatives who are widows, she must
        take care of them and not put the responsibility on the church. Then the
        church can care for the widows who are truly alone.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Elders who do their work well should be respected and paid well,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        especially those who work hard at both preaching and teaching. '
      comments:
      - number: '5:17 '
        content: Greek <b>should be worthy of double honor.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "For the Scripture says, \u201CYou must not muzzle an ox to keep it
        from eating as it treads out the grain.\u201D And in another place, \u201CThose
        who work deserve their pay!\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:18 '
        content: Deut 25:4; Luke 10:7.
    - title: 
      content: 'Do not listen to an accusation against an elder unless it is confirmed
        by two or three witnesses. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those who sin should be reprimanded in front of the whole church;
        this will serve as a strong warning to others.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I solemnly command you in the presence of God and Christ Jesus and
        the highest angels to obey these instructions without taking sides or showing
        favoritism to anyone.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Never be in a hurry about appointing a church leader.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Do not share in the sins of others. Keep yourself pure.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:22 '
        content: Greek <b>about the laying on of hands.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t drink only water. You ought to drink a little wine for
        the sake of your stomach because you are sick so often.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Remember, the sins of some people are obvious, leading them to certain
        judgment. But there are others whose sins will not be revealed until later. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  All slaves should show full respect for their masters so they will
        not bring shame on the name of God and his teaching. '
      comments: []
    - title: False Teaching and True Riches
      content: 'If the masters are believers, that is no excuse for being disrespectful.
        Those slaves should work all the harder because their efforts are helping
        other believers[[COMMENT(0)]] who are well loved.Teach these things, Timothy,
        and encourage everyone to obey them. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:2 '
        content: Greek <b>brothers.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Some people may contradict our teaching, but these are the wholesome
        teachings of the Lord Jesus Christ. These teachings promote a godly life. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Anyone who teaches something different is arrogant and lacks understanding.
        Such a person has an unhealthy desire to quibble over the meaning of words.
        This stirs up arguments ending in jealousy, division, slander, and evil suspicions. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These people always cause trouble. Their minds are corrupt, and they
        have turned their backs on the truth. To them, a show of godliness is just
        a way to become wealthy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet true godliness with contentment is itself great wealth. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "After all, we brought nothing with us when we came into the world,
        and we can\u2019t take anything with us when we leave it. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So if we have enough food and clothing, let us be content.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But people who long to be rich fall into temptation and are trapped
        by many foolish and harmful desires that plunge them into ruin and destruction. '
      comments: []
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Final Instructions"
      content: 'For the love of money is the root of all kinds of evil. And some
        people, craving money, have wandered from the true faith and pierced themselves
        with many sorrows.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you, Timothy, are a man of God; so run from all these evil things.
        Pursue righteousness and a godly life, along with faith, love, perseverance,
        and gentleness. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Fight the good fight for the true faith. Hold tightly to the eternal
        life to which God has called you, which you have declared so well before
        many witnesses. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And I charge you before God, who gives life to all, and before Christ
        Jesus, who gave a good testimony before Pontius Pilate, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'that you obey this command without wavering. Then no one can find
        fault with you from now until our Lord Jesus Christ comes again. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For,At just the right time Christ will be revealed from heaven by
        the blessed and only almighty God, the King of all kings and Lord of all
        lords. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He alone can never die, and he lives in light so brilliant that no
        human can approach him. No human eye has ever seen him, nor ever will. All
        honor and power to him forever! Amen.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Teach those who are rich in this world not to be proud and not to
        trust in their money, which is so unreliable. Their trust should be in God,
        who richly gives us all we need for our enjoyment. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Tell them to use their money to do good. They should be rich in good
        works and generous to those in need, always being ready to share with others. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'By doing this they will be storing up their treasure as a good foundation
        for the future so that they may experience true life.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Timothy, guard what God has entrusted to you. Avoid godless, foolish
        discussions with those who oppose you with their so-called knowledge. '
      comments: []
